summary: This document is an FBI evidence inventory record listing one FBI-owned Western Digital hard drive containing multiple digital images, likely seized as part of the Epstein investigation. It appears to catalog evidence items with reference numbers.
keyFacts: The FBI seized a Western Digital hard drive (model WD3003FZEX-0024SA0, serial number MiCC13LZR5) containing multiple digital images.
The evidence inventory was created on August 21, 2019, indicating ongoing evidence processing in the Epstein case.
The document references multiple evidence item numbers (NYCO23578 through NYCO23592) associated with the images on the hard drive.
The hard drive is described as 'FBI-owned', suggesting it may be a forensic copy or evidence storage device rather than original seized media.
